1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:06,640
In 1943, a dead man washed ashore in Spain, and changed the entire course of World War II.

2
00:00:06,590 --> 00:00:12,477
Operation Mincemeat was a top-secret British plan to trick Nazi Germany before the invasion of Sicily.

3
00:00:12,477 --> 00:00:18,488
They strapped fake war plans to a corpse dressed as a Royal Marines officer, a man who never existed.

4
00:00:18,488 --> 00:00:25,999
The body belonged to a 34-year-old homeless Welsh man named Glyndwr Michael, who had died from eating rat poison.

5
00:00:25,999 --> 00:00:31,409
If the Nazis spotted the forgery, thousands of Allied soldiers would sail straight into a trap.

6
00:00:31,409 --> 00:00:37,374
Hitler was so convinced, he moved an entire Panzer division to Greece, away from the real target.

7
00:00:37,374 --> 00:00:44,454
When the Allies invaded Sicily, they faced dramatically weakened defenses, saving an estimated 40,000 lives.

8
00:00:44,454 --> 00:00:47,738
The operation stayed classified for decades.

9
00:00:47,738 --> 00:00:52,159
The dead man's true identity wasn't confirmed until 1996.

10
00:00:52,159 --> 00:00:54,863
Could one dead man really have won a war?

11
00:00:54,863 --> 00:00:56,636
Follow for more.

